<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>CEI Staff: Tom Miller</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="009900" VLINK="000099">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLPADDING=15><TR><TD>

<IMG SRC="/images/staff/miller.gif" WIDTH=126 HEIGHT=187 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=13 VSPACE=5 BORDER=1>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT>


<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Tom Miller</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Director of Economic Policy Studies<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:tmiller@CEI.org">tmiller@CEI.org</A></B>
</CENTER>

<P>
<BR>
Tom Miller is the Director of <A HREF="/errp.html">Economic Policy Studies</A> at the <A HREF="/">Competitive
Enterprise Institute</A>, a non-partisan public interest group committed to
advancing the principles of free enterprise and limited government.  Based
in Washington, D.C., the Institute is founded on the belief that free
markets and individual liberty  best serve the public interest, while
politicians and bureaucrats best serve themselves.  

<P>Mr. Miller directs the <A HREF="/errp.html">Economic Policy and Regulatory Reform program</A> at CEI.
As CEI's Senior Policy Analyst since 1986, his primary focus has been on
issues of financial services regulation, health care insurance, entitlement
programs reform, and antitrust regulation.  Mr. Miller is the author of <I>A Citizen's Guide To Banking Reform</I>, described by Representative Dick Armey as "A lucid, rigorous, and refreshingly accessible treatment of a complicated
and important subject." He is editor of the annual Competitive Enterprise
Index, which analyzes all congressional votes judged to have a significant
impact on competition, freedom, and opportunity in the U.S. economy. 

<P>Prior to joining CEI, Mr. Miller was a trial attorney, a broadcaster, and a
journalist.  At the firm of Powell, Goldstein, Frazer & Murphy in Atlanta,
his litigation activities included personal injury, insurance defense,
criminal defense, medical malpractice, and copyright cases.  Mr. Miller was
a news director at radio stations in Rome, Georgia and Anderson, South
Carolina; a sportscaster and talk show host at radio stations in Charlotte,
North Carolina and Atlanta; a writer/producer for current affairs programs
at the Voice of America; and a consulting producer for two television
programs, "The McLaughlin Group" and "John McLaughlin One-on-One."  Mr.
Miller was also a free lance writer on continuing assignment for <I>Reader's Digest</I> and an investigative reporter for syndicated columnist Donald Lambro.  

<P>Mr. Miller received his law degree from Duke Law School and a B.A. cum laude
in political science from New York University.  He is a member of the State
Bar of Georgia.   

<P>Mr. Miller's work on public policy issues has appeared in such publications
as <I>The Wall Street Journal, Reader's Digest, Reason, American Spectator,
Insight, Consumers Research, Los Angeles Times, Washington Times</I>, and
<I>Cleveland Plain Dealer</I>.

<P>See these articles by Tom Miller available on-line :
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/update/0896-tm.html">"The Political Economy of MSAs"</A>
<LI><A HREF="/update/0796-tm.html">"MSAs -- Panacea or Placebo?</A>
<LI><A HREF="/miller.html">"Portability -- A Trojan Pony"</A>
</UL>

<P>Contact Tom Miller at <A HREF="mailto:tmiller@CEI.org">tmiller@CEI.org</A>.


</TD></TR></TABLE>
