<TITLE>Welcome to Wells, Maine</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="gifs/wellstile.gif" TEXT=#000000 LINK="#aa372c" VLINK="#338262">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A HREF="/cgi-bin/imagemap/~fitch/maps/wellstoolbar.map" BORDER=0 ><IMG WIDTH=140 HEIGHT=488 SRC="gifs/wellstoolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
				<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=486>
				<TR>		
				<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
				<IMG WIDTH=486 HEIGHT=110 SRC="gifs/wellshome.gif">
				</TD></TR><TR>
				<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<IMG SRC="gifs/wellsdropcap.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>ells has many vacation pleasures to tempt its summer visitors.  Here you will find miles of white sandy beaches to loll on,  rocky coastline and tidepools full of marine treasures for the kids explore.  Zip around town on your rented Moped, visit the harbor, or comb the dozens of fine antiques stores for a treasure or two to commemorate your visit.<P> <img src="gifs/harbor.gif" ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
And who can resist the temptation of succulent lobster rolls at a sunny table on a deck? Wells has many fine restaurants to choose from, and visitors to Wells can find anything from fine seafood and steak dinners, to casual clambake dining, to homemade ice cream treats!  Stay for a day, a long weekend, or your whole summer vacation,  and enjoy the classic New England charms of sun, fun, shopping, and feasting!
<P>
We are glad to welcome you to the Wells Web Information Center. Enjoy our web sites, and be sure to visit our official online Town Offices.  Put a bookmark on Community Network for future reference; we update frequently, and if you use these sites to plan your trip let us know by posting us an email.
</TD>
				</TR>
				</TABLE>
</TD>
</TR>

