<TITLE>Welcome to Haiku, Maui</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF TEXT=#000000 LINK="#aa372c" VLINK="#338262">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=550>
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=182 HEIGHT=70 SRC="gifs/img3.gif"><IMG WIDTH=383 HEIGHT=70 SRC="gifs/img4.gif" ALT="Heavenly Haiku"></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD><IMG  ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=316 HEIGHT=171 SRC="gifs/img1.gif"></TD>
<TD WIDTH=236 HEIGHT=171 ALIGN LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=1 Height=1  SRC="gifs/dot.gif"><BR>
Aloha! Thanks for your inquiry.  What we have is two bedrooms, each with a private bath, and both bedrooms share a kitchenette. The rooms are non-smoking. 
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=197 Height=370 SRC="gifs/img2.gif">
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADING=0>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT>To insure our guest's privacy, we only rent out 1 of the rooms, unless there are two couples traveling together.<P>
Each room opens onto a large (8' by 35') covered lanai that 
has tables, chairs and a BBQ, and a view of Haleakala 
Mountain. One room is 14' by 17' with a mountain and ocean 
view; the other is slightly smaller with a mountain view only.
The rate for the room is $55 per night single or double, with 
a large closet, dresser, and queen bed. If you need the second 
room, add $35 per night. Everything is new and very clean. 
This is in a private wing of our very large home, so we keep 
it very nice, and you have your own private entrance.If you 
have been to Maui before, you will be familiar with the areas 
of Maui; we are in the community of Haiku, which is on the 
North side of the island. Very green and tropical due to lots 
of rainfall, thankfully mostly at night. We are in the country, 
rural and very quiet. Not a resort setting. You are bout 3 
minutes away from the nearest small grocery store, 6 
minutes from excellent restaurants in the town of Makawao, 
15 minutes from Ho'okipa, and 25 minutes from Kanaha.
<P>
For information contact: <I><A HREF="mailto:horstman@maui.net">horstman@maui.net</A></I>
