<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Directions</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="gifs/wellsback.gif">
<P>
<H1>Getting to the area </H1>
<P>
<IMG SRC="Wells_Directions1.jpeg"></STRONG>
<P>
<H2>Directions to Ogunquit </H2><P>
From the North the major high way is the Maine Turnpike! (or Route 
95) Take Exit 2, the Wells exit and turn right on Route 1. Follow Route 1 and you will end up in Ogunquit. 
<P>
For the South get off Route 95 before reaching the Maine Turnpike. It will be the last exit before the toll. After take a right off the exit and then take a left at the 
first light. You will then be heading North on Route 1 which will take you to the center of Ogunquit.<P>
<P>
<H2>Directions to Kennebunk/Kennebunkport </H2><P>
The major high way is the Maine Turnpike! (or Route 
95) Take Exit 3, the Kennebunk exit. After leaving the toll booth take Route 9 East. The next light you will be in the center of Kennebunk. Wells and Ogunquit 
to your right, Arundel and Biddeford to your left! Go through the lights and follow route 9 until you reach a second light. At that light take a left and you will cross the bridge into Kennebunkport<P>
<P>
<H2>Directions to Wells </H2><P>
From either direction Wells' only major high way is the Maine Turnpike! (or Route 
95) Take Exit 2, the Wells exit. After leaving the toll booth take a left at the 
first light. The next light you will be in the center of Wells. Kennebunk and Kennebunkport to your left, Ogunquit and York to your right!<P>
<P>
<H2>Directions to Kittery </H2><P>
From either direction Kitterys' major highways are Route 95 taking Exit 1 or 2, the Kittery exits, and Route 1. If you reach the toll booth for the Maine turnpike you have passed the exits for Kittery going North. If you reach the Bridge for New Hampshire you have passed Kittery going to far South.<P>
<P><H2>Directions to York </H2><P>
From either direction Yorks' major highway is Route 95. If you reach the toll booth for the Maine turnpike you have passed the exit for York going North. The York exit is the last exit before the toll booth. If you reach the Bridge for New Hampshire you have passed York going to far South. York is the first exit after the tool booth going South.<P>
<P><IMG SRC="Wells_Directions2.jpeg"><P>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>Nearby local communities</H2>
<CENTER> <TABLE BORDER=2> <TR> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/kbunk/kbunk.html">
<BR>
Kennebunk</A> </TD> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/kport/kport.html">
<BR>
Kennebunkport</A> </TD> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/kittery/kittery.html">
<BR>
Kittery</A> </TD> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/ogunquit/ogunquit.html">
<BR>
Ogunquit</A> </TD> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/wells/wells.html">
<BR>
Wells</A> </TD> <TD Align=center ><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/york/york.html">
<BR>
York</A> </TD></TR> </TABLE> <HR>
<BR>
