<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Marginal Way</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="gifs/ogunquitback.gif">
<P>
<H1>Welcome to the Marginal Way</H1>
<HR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="winterway.gif" align=center><BR> Little Beach Marginal Way <P>
The Marginal Way (an old Indian 
trail) takes you along the rocky Maine coast and ends at <A HREF="http://www.sirius.com/~fitch/ogunquit/pcove.html">Perkins Cove</A>. The footpath is a beautiful elevation of land which resides just Southwest of the village of Ogunquit. It follows the shoreline and is a must for any visitor to the area.
<P>
While on a stroll down the Marginal Way stop and ponder how it used to be! Just look at the picture to the right and you can see how many other people have moved into the area to also enjoy this beautiful seashore community. One can see why so many <A HREF="http://www.sirius.com/~fitch/ogunquit/art.html">artists</A> have opted to spend time as this Beautiful Place By The Sea.<BR>
<IMG SRC="mway.jpeg" align=center><BR><P>
<HR>
