<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Perkins Cove</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="gifs/ogunquitback.gif">
<P>
<H1>Welcome to Perkins Cove</H1>
<HR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="ogunquit8.jpeg"> Perkins Cove at dusk <P>
Perkins Cove is one of Ogunquit's most beautiful spots. The Marginal Way (an old Indian 
trail) takes you along the rocky Maine coast and ends (or begins) here. 
<P>
<H5>How it all Began </H5>
Perkins Cove started out as a small fishing community! It was the place where men 
set off to sea for their daily haul! From the cove men made their traps and fixed 
their lines and nets.
<P><CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=10><TR><TD>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="ogunquit6.jpeg" WIDTH=200 HIEGHT=150><BR>Perkins Cove 1930</CENTER></TD>
<TD><CENTER>
<IMG SRC="ogunquit7.jpeg" WIDTH=200 HIEGHT=150><BR>Perkins Cove 1940</CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
As time wore on not only the fishermen noticed the beauty of the cove. More and More 
stores and restaurants moved in bringing in more visitors to also share this wonderful 
part of Ogunquit.
<P>
(Notice the footbridge is in each of these photos. It has changed it's appearance 
but always remained. Just like many of the restaurants in Perkins Cove!)
<P>
Like...
<CENTER><TABLE CELLSPACING=20><TR><TD><CENTER><IMG SRC="oarweed/oarweed.gif" WIDTH="106" HEIGHT="69" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"0" ALIGN=bottom><BR>Johnny's Oarweed</CENTER></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.bunnyclark.com" BORDER=0><CENTER><IMG SRC="billy/bunny.gif"ALIGN=bottom BORDER=0><BR>Bunny Clark</CENTER></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/ogunquit/billy/barnaclebillys.html" BORDER=0><CENTER><IMG SRC="billy/bbsign.gif" WIDTH="106" HEIGHT="69" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"0" ALIGN=bottom BORDER=0><BR>Barnacle Billy's</A></CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER
<BR>
<HR>
