<HEAD>
<TITLE>Welcome to Ogunquit, Maine</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="gifs/ogunquittile.gif" TEXT=#000000 LINK="#aa372c" VLINK="#338262">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A HREF="/cgi-bin/imagemap/~fitch/maps/ogunquittoolbar.map" BORDER=0 ><IMG WIDTH=140 HEIGHT=488 SRC="gifs/ogunquittoolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
				<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=486>
				<TR>		
				<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
				<IMG WIDTH=486 HEIGHT=110 SRC="gifs/ogunquithome.gif">
				</TD></TR><TR><TD>
				<CENTER>Index to Ogunquit Web Site</CENTER><BR>
				This page will be a reference point for the Ogunquit site. Here you can navigate quickly to find the information you need very easily. Also the toolbar on the left can be used to get to certain informative categories.<P>
We hope you will enjoy the site!<P>
<H4><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/wells/wellsd.html">Directions</H4></A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/ogunquit/business/ogunquitbiz.html">Business Directory</H4></A><BR>
Although summer is the busy season in Ogunquit there are now more reasons
to visit in the off-season. A cozy room at one of Ogunquit's hotels or bed
and breakfasts is a great way to escape that city hustle. Shops are less
crowded and the town seems a little more inviting.<BR>
<BR>
Ogunquit is a beautiful coastal town that has much to offer. Please browse
our page and visit the various topics that may be of any interest. Make
plans before you get to the area through our sponsors. Many businesses will
be listed here with varying degrees of information and available services.
<BR>
</TD>
				</TR>
				</TABLE>
</TD>
