<TITLE>Wells Police Department: Chief William H. Zackular</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="gifs/tile2.gif" TEXT=#000000 LINK=#O000A2 VLINK=#B20000>
<CENTER>

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=508>

<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=3><A HREF="/cgi-bin/imagemap/~fitch/maps/toolbar1.map" BORDER=0 ><IMG WIDTH=508 HEIGHT=97 SRC="gifs/toolbar1.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=269 SRC="gifs/invisible.gif"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=214 HEIGHT=269 SRC="gifs/williamhzackular.gif"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
William Zackular has been Chief of Wells Police Department since 1986. Prior to `86 he was a police officer in the Town of Scarborough. He has been a patrolman, detective, K-9 handler, sergeant, and lieutenant. Chief Zackular graduated from fhe FBI National Academy in Quantico, Virginia in 1954. He is a certified Criminal Justice Educator and State certified Police Dog Trainer.
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=83 SRC="gifs/invisible.gif"></TD>
<TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
Your education is one of the most important parts of your life. What you get out of it is what you put into it.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/wells/gvt/police/police.html">Back to Wells Police Department Index.</A>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>
