<TD COLSPAN=3><A HREF="/cgi-bin/imagemap/~fitch/maps/toolbar2.map" BORDER=0 ><IMG WIDTH=508 HEIGHT=97 SRC="gifs/toolbar2.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=269 SRC="gifs/invisible.gif"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=214 HEIGHT=269 SRC="gifs/richardconnelly.gif"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
Captain Connelly lives in Wells and has been with the police department for 18 years. Five of these years were spent on loan to the State Drug Unit where he served as an undercover officer and then officer supervisor. He was promoted to Captain in 1994 and is in charge of all police operations. He has a BA in Criminal Justice and enjoys spending time with his family.
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=83 SRC="gifs/invisible.gif"></TD>
<TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<B>Safety Tip:</B> Don't be afraid to be different and stick up for what you believe in and know in your heart is right. The right way isn't always the easiest way. Others will watch you and respect you. Remember to treat others as you would have them treat you.
<P>
