<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Nutrition for Life Home Page</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#fbdcaf" TEXT="#69346e"><A NAME="anchortop"></A><H2><CENTER>Nutrition for Life!</H2><BR><IMG SRC="v1.gif" WIDTH="132" HEIGHT="190" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN=bottomBORDER="1"></CENTER><H3><CENTER>Email: <A HREF="mailto:Jojanjove@aol.com">Jojanjove@aol.com</A><BR>Phone: 207 646-0578</CENTER></H3><HR SIZE="10"><BR>Hello, my name is Velma Farnsworth and welcome to the Nutrition for Life Home Page. I am a registered dietitian with the American Dietetic Association (ADA) and licensed with the State of Maine. My education includes a B.S. degree in foods and human nutrition, and an M.S. degree in human nutrition. <BR><BR>My nutrition couseling service recognizes the individual's goal in his/her pursuit of good health. Menus and meal patterns are designed to consider lifestyle, daily nutrition and energy requirements, level of food prepartion expertise and special nutrition requirements related to existing medical conditions.<BR><BR>I hope you find my home page informative, helpful and convenient. Many of my clients enjoy communicating via the Internet. I hope you do also!<B><BR><BR>Be sure to check out the 'Current Nutrition Topics Intepreted' this month. I cover the pros and cons of the recently FDA approved fat substitute &quot;Olestra&quot;.</B><MENU>Nutrient Analysis of Existing Food Intake With Recommendations toMeet Individuals Daily Requirements<BR><BR>Meal Preparation Classes and Consulting for Good Health<BR><BR>Clinical Nutrition Counseling For Individuals<BR><BR><A HREF="#anchormenu">Daily Menus Designed With Accompanying Recipes And Shopping Lists</A><BR><BR>Group Sessions For Eating Disorders And Compulsive Eating<BR><BR><A HREF="#anchortopics">Current Nutrition Topics Interpreted (Olestra, FDA approved fat substitute)</A></MENU><HR SIZE="7" WIDTH="85%"><CENTER><IMG SRC="image1.gif" WIDTH="184" HEIGHT="237" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN=bottom><BR><BR><P><HR><A NAME="anchortopics"></A><H2>Current Nutrition Topics Interpreted</CENTER></H2><BR>This month I would like to discuss Olestra, a new fat substitute chemicalcompound approved by the Food and Drug Administration in January, 1996.<DL><DD>Olestra will be marketed by Proctor and Gamble under the name &quot;Olean&quot;.It will be used in savory snacks such as potato chips, corn chips, cheesepuffs and crackers. Similar to other food choices there are both positiveand negative impacts on the body to consider. </DL></DD><BR><BR><A HREF="mailto:Jojanjove@aol.com">Email me to receive my complete nutritional analysis of Olestra (&quot;Olean&quot;).<BR></A><BR><BR><H3><CENTER>Thank you for visiting the Nutrition For Life Home Page.</CENTER></H3><H3><HR></H3><CENTER><A NAME="anchormenu"></A><H2>Daily Menu</H2><BR><BR><H2>BREAKFAST</H2><DL>1 small banana<BR>1 ounce cereal<BR>8 ounces skim milk </DL><H2>LUNCH</H2><H3>Salmon salad platter</H3><DL>3 ounces pink salmon<BR>red pepper rings<BR>sweet onion and lemon wedge on bed of lettuce<BR>1 hard roll<BR>1 tablespoon salad dressing<BR>1 citrus fruit<BR>8 ounces skim milk </DL><H2>DINNER</H2><DL>1 serving &quot;chicken cacciatore&quot; <B>*</B><BR>1 cup rice<BR>1 serving tossed salad<BR>1 tablespoon salad dressing<BR>1 cup &quot;apple snow&quot; <B>*<BR><BR>*</B> recipe available<BR><HR WIDTH="80%"></CENTER></DD></DL><CENTER><B><A HREF="mailto:Jojanjove@aol.com">Email Nutrition For Life</A><BR><BR></A><A HREF="#anchortopics">Current Topics</A> - <A HREF="#anchortop">Topof Page<BR><BR></A>Thank you for visiting the Nutrition For Life Home Page.</B></CENTER><BR><HR><P><CENTER>This page created by <BR><A HREF="http://www.communitynetwork.com/cmn/cmn.html"><IMG SRC="http://www.communitynetwork.com/cmn/image3.gif"></A></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
