<HEAD>
    <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="../gifs/ogunquitback.gif">
<H1></H1>
<H1><CENTER>Welcome to </H1>

<H2><IMG SRC="bbsign.gif" WIDTH="175" HEIGHT="91" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
@ Perkins Cove, Ogunquit, Maine</H2>
</CENTER> <HR SIZE="11">
<B>Barnacle Billy's has been a family run restaurant anchored in Perkins
Cove harbor for decades. People come for the coladas, daqueries,
and sunsets. At the cove-end of Marginal Way, a stop at &quot;Billy's&quot;
might mean, sitting on the sunset lit deck sipping frozen drinks and feasting
on aromas of lobster, or, it could mean an ice cream cone and and a stroll
around the loop. <BR>
<P><CENTER>Perkins Cove also is home to one of the oldest foot drawbridges
in New England.<BR>
<BR>
 Here's how it looks while you're all in Florida this winter!</B></CENTER>
<P>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="footbridge.gif" WIDTH="320" HEIGHT="240" ALIGN=bottom
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"></CENTER>
<P><HR>
<H4>Barnacle Billy makes no qualm with the fact that people say &quot;its
the lobster rolls and the deck&quot; that keeps 'em coming back.</H4>
<BR>
<H3><CENTER>Sorry folks, we're closed right now.<BR>
Spring is almost here, come see us this then!</CENTER>
</H3>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="winterbilly.gif" WIDTH="320" HEIGHT="240" ALIGN=bottom
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="3"></CENTER>
<H3><BR>
<BR>
<CENTER> Your host - Billy Tower.<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="tunatower.gif" WIDTH="191" HEIGHT="296" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3" BORDER="1"></H3>
<H3>Other Perkins Cove related sites</CENTER>
</H3>
<CENTER>
