<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpading=10>
<tr><td width=15%><A href="bemag.html"><img src="images/be4.gif" border=0></a></
td>
<td>
<table border=0 cellpading=1 cellspacing=5>
<tr>
<td><i><font size=+3>B</font><font size=+2>USINESS</font> <font size=+3>E</font><font size=+2>UROPA</font></i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i><font size=+3>I</font><font size=+2>NTRODUCTION</font></i></td>
</tr>
</table>
</tr>
</table>
<form method=post action=http://www.ipl.co.uk/cgi-bin/gen4>
<br>
<b>BUSINESS EUROPA</b> gives you Central Europe - minus the mystery.<p>

<b>First in the field: Business Europa,</b> the original regional magazine entirely devoted to coverage of business developments in Central and Eastern Europe.<p>

<b>Regular check-list:</b> the central feature of the magazine is its <a href="besummy.html">regional brief</a>, a country by country check-list of key business and economic developments in recent weeks.  Who's bought whom, for how much. Who's invested in whom.  Who's started, who's stopped.  This regular feature is a <i>must read</i> for anyone with an active interest in the region, an opportunity to catch up on events that may have been missed, overlooked or plain forgotten.<p>
<b>Lively features:</b> on a wide and varied range of topics, including Hungarian Wine, the Danube's ecology, Czech Beer, Macedonia, Kosice, Krakow, Slovenia.  <b>Business Europa</b> is the most readable source of business information on the region.  Never dull, always interesting.<p>
<b>Reliable information:</b> other regular features include book reviews, a calendar of events - fairs, conferences, exhibitions etc., key indicators and data on all the region's major economies.<p>
<hr size=2>
<blockquote>
<b>Business Europa</b><br>
2 Market Street, Saffron Walden, Essex CB10 1HZ, UK.<br>
Fax: +44 (0)1799 524805<br>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:waldenpub@easynet.co.uk">waldenpub@easynet.co.uk</a> 
</blockquote>

