<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#FF0000" alink="#000000" vlink="#0000ff">

<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1996.</i></font><br>

<img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="bccroat.html">Select Winter 1995</a></center>
<h3>CROATIA</h3>

The Croatian Ambassador to the USA, Mario Nobilo went on the offensive in March over claims of violence and intimidation against Serbs living in the Krajina area of Croatia. In a statement defending the capture of the region in 1995 he compared the incidence of violence and robbery against American citizens to reported incidents in Krajina, with residents of Miami more than four times as likely to be victims of violent crime as those living in Krajina.
<P>
Industrial output in the first two months of 1996 saw a 3.5 per cent increase on the same period last year, according to the State Institute for Statistics.
<P>
Croatia's external debt increased by US$400 million to US$3.2 billion in 1995, excluding the country's share of the foreign debt of the former Yugoslavia.
<P>
The first Croatian firm to launch a global share offer, the drug company Pliva, has seen strong interest from international investors.


<p>
