<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>BELARUS</h3>

The national referendum on Sunday 14 May saw 82.4 per cent of voters express their preference for 
economic union with Russia. Integration has been presented by the Lukeshenko administration as the only 
viable option for reversing the country's continued economic decline. <p>

<b>Ford</b> of the USA is proceeding with plans to establish a passenger vehicle assembly plant in 
Belarus. Production is expected to start in late 1996 or early 1997. <p> 

Belarus has had a new telephone dialling code since 16 April. The old Soviet code of 7 has been dropped, 
to be replaced by 375. The code for Minsk is 172 instead of 0172.<p>  
