<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#FF0000" alink="#000000" vlink="#0000ff">

<center><i><font size=+2>W</font><font size=+1>inter 1995.</i></font><br>

<img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="bbcroat.html">Select Summer 1995</a></center>

<h3>CROATIA</h3>

Industrial output in Croatia rose by 2 per cent in May according to figures issued by the Central Bureau of Statistics. The year-on-year change was 1 per cent. The Republic's trade deficit in May was US$21 million, a deterioration from April's US$3 million deficit, but less than half May 1994's figure of US$48 million.
<p>
The Agro-Obrtnicka Banka commercial bank is to receive a loan of 10 million marks from the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) to support medium to long-term investment projects in the agricultural sector.
<p>
The World Bank is reportedly planning to grant Croatia a loan of between US$80-100 million in November 1995. The loan is to cover bank rehabilitation, privatisation and restructuring of public companies.
<p>
<hr>
<center><img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="besummy.html">Summary Menu</a></center>

