<center><i><font size=+2>W</font><font size=+1>inter 1995.</i></font><br>
</center>

<h3>GEORGIA</h3>
The lari, Georgia's new unit of currency, came into circulation on 26 September 1995 and became sole legal tender on 2 October 1995. The initial exchange rate for the lari is 1.3 to the dollar.
<p>
Following the 29 August assassination attempt on President Eduard Shevardnadze the commanding officer of Georgia's Alpha special security unit, Gela Papuashvili was arrested in late September. It was reported that explosives, detonators and timing devices had been found in the police chief's apartment. Later reports suggested that the attempt had been planned by former security minister Igor Georgadze with Russian support.
<p>
<hr>
<center><img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="besummy.html">Summary Menu</a></center>

</center>
