<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>SERBIA & MONTENEGRO</h3>

In late March the Serbian government was obliged to shore up the dinar by denying rumours of an 
imminent devaluation. The dinar, introduced in January 1994, is officially pegged at DM1, but in March 
dropped to a rate of 4.5 to the DM, subsequently stabilising at 2.6 to the DM. <b>Central Bank</b> 
governor Dragoslav Avramovic claimed that there had been no change in the government's tight monetary 
policy.
<p> 

<hr>
<center><img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="besummy.html">Summary Menu</a></center>

</center>
<hr size=3>
<h5>This site is hosted by <a href="http://www.ipl.co.uk/">Information Providers Limited</a>,
<i>Tel:</i> +44 (0) 1689 860000, <i>Fax:</i> +44 (0) 1689 860330
