<HEAD>
<title>Business Euro</title>
<!version 1.00>
<HTML>
<meta name="description" value="Business Euro">
<meta name "Admin-Email" value="mxp@ipl.co.uk">
<meta name "keywords" value="Industry, Political, Structure, Facts">
<!--File name buseu13.html-->
<!--Last update 17/August/95-->
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#FF0000" alink="#000000" vlink="#0000ff">

<P>
<CENTER>
<h2>Armed Forces</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
According to recent estimates the Bulgarian armed forces consists of 99,000 
active personnel including about 60,000 conscripts. There are 12,000 border 
guards in 12 regiments as well as 4,000 security police. The period of 
service is 18 months.
<P>
The army, which has 52,000 people, about 33,000 of whom are conscripts, has 
four tank brigades and three motor rifle divisions. It is equipped with 
1,277 T 55 tanks, as well as 599 T 34s and 333 T 72s. The army's total 
artillery is 2,081. It has 67 surface to air missiles and 72 surface to 
surface missile launchers (including 36 Scud).
<P>
The navy, with its main base at Varna, is made up of 3,000 personnel, 2,000 
of whom are conscripts. Other coastal bases are at Atiya, Sozopol and 
Balchik in addition to Vidin on the Danube. The fleet consists of one 
frigate and two submarines of the `Romeo' class. There are three small 
frigates, nine corvettes, six missile craft, four torpedo craft, five 
coastal patrol vessels, 10 minelayers, 18 minesweepers, seven patrol vessels 
and 10 armed helicopters.
<P>
The airforce has 21,800 personnel in two air divisions, one mixed air 
corps and 6 combat regiments. There are 16,000 conscripts. The airforce has 
275 combat aircraft and 44 attack helicopters. It has three fighter 
regiments with about 22 MiG 23, 108 MiG 21 fast patrol craft and 22 MiG 29 
aircraft. As well, there is one fighter ground attack regiment with 39 Su 25 
aircraft and one regiment with 37 MiG 23. There is one reconnaissance 
regiment with 47 aircraft (26 MiG 23 and 21 Su 22) and two helicopter 
regiments with 14 Mi 2, 25 Mi 17 and 44 Mi 24 helicopters. For transport, 
the airforce has one regiment with two Tu 134, three An 24, four An 26, 
five L 410 and three Yak 40 (VIP).
<P>
Bulgaria has a relatively sophisticated arms industry supplying most of the 
country's needs. There is emphasis on high tech developments such as the 
laser duel simulator surveillance device for tank crews, the latest aerial 
target equipment, barrage jammers (tested in the Gulf War) and radarproof 
steel bridges.
<P>
The arms industry was planning to switch the manufacture of AK 47 assault 
rifles of 5.45mm calibre to the NATO standard 5.56mm.
<P>
Despite these technological advances, large scale redundancies are imminent 
in the defence industry (once one of eastern Europe's largest).
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<center><IMG SRC="images/pinred.gif"> <A HREF="bsmenu.html">Bulgaria Subjects</A></center>
