GMT plus two hours (GMT plus three hours from late March to late September)
<P>
<a name="Languages"></a>
<hr>
<a href="#List"><img src="images/arrowup.gif" alt="Top" align=right border=0></a>
<h3>Languages Spoken</h3>
Ukrainian is the official language; Russian is widely spoken; Romanian, Polish, Hungarian
also spoken. Only about half of all Ukrainians speak Ukrainian, with the majority in the east
speaking Russian.
<P>
<a name="Currency"></a>
<hr>
<a href="#List"><img src="images/arrowup.gif" alt="Top" align=right border=0></a>
<h3>Currency</h3>
Karbovanets (Krb) (interim currency coupon) (plural Karbovantsi) introduced 16 November
1992. The most commonly used notes are the 20,000, 50,000 and 100,000 notes; the 500,
1,000, 5,000 and 10,000 karbovanets notes are virtually worthless. Hryvnia to be introduced
in 1996.
