<P>
<a name="Taxation"></a>
<hr>
<a href="#List"><img src="images/arrowup.gif" alt="Top" align=right border=0></a>
<h3>Taxation</h3>
<b>Corporate taxation system</b>
<P>
From 1 January 1995 the basic rate of profit tax is 30 per cent. Gambling enterprises are taxed at 60 per cent and agricultural enterprises providing services for agricultural production at 15 per cent. The law abolished five-year tax holidays for enterprises with foreign investment registered after 1 January 1995. Certain activities (agricultural production and processing, fishing and fish processing, rural construction) are exempt from profit tax.
<P>
Enterprises meeting the following criteria are also exempt from tax:
obtain all their revenue from outside Ukraine<br>
have a management and administration of entirely Ukrainian citizens
make their settlements only through Ukrainian banks.<br>
The standard rate of value added tax (VAT) is 20 per cent, payable on the majority of goods and services except insurance, reinsurance and education.<br>
A 37 per cent payroll tax payable by employers finances the social and pension funds. An additional 12 per cent tax on wages finances the Chernobyl and unemployment funds.<br> Employees are liable for 1 per cent of their wages for the pension fund and 3 per cent for the Chernobyl fund.
<P>
<b>Personal taxation</b>
<P>
The maximum personal rate of income tax is 30 per cent.
In February 1996 agricultural workers were exempted from paying income tax on payments in kind. The resolution passed by parliament will raise real wages in the sector which are lower than any other sector.

<a href="#Top"><img src="images/arrowup.gif" alt="List" align=right border=0></a>
<P>
