<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>ARMENIA</h3>

Parliamentary elections are scheduled to be held in Armenia on 5 July 1995.<p> 

London's <b>Financial Times</b> published a four page special report on Armenia on 7 June 1995. <p>

Sixty-four per cent of shares in Armenia's 10 largest enterprises are to be sold for a mixture of 
privatisation certificates and cash, according to the Armenian <b>Privatisation Commission</b>. The 
companies include the country's only car plant, an electrical equipment plant and a pastry producer. The 
enterprises are to be converted into joint stock companies open to foreign investment.<p>

Armenia has a new telephone/fax dialling code. Since 1 May the old Soviet prefix of 7 has been dropped, 
to be replaced with 374. 
