<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#FF0000" alink="#000000" vlink="#0000ff">
<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>AZERBAIJAN</h3> 

The oil consortium led by <b>British Petroleum</b> (UK) and Statoil (Norway) expects to start 
production in mid 1996 and exports by the end of 1996. Before then a decision has to be taken as to the 
route of the pipeline to export the crude. The choice appears to lie between a northerly route developed in 
association with Transneft of Russia or an alternative route to the Black Sea in association with Georgia. 
Plans for the exports to pass through Iran have been quashed by the project's US shareholders, as has the 
possibility of Iran taking a 5 per cent stake in the project.<p>

<b>British Airways</b> has introduced a twice-weekly London (Gatwick) - Baku service, via Bucharest. 
The service is operated by Boeing 737-400s with a return fare of US$1,400.

