<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer1995.</i></font><br>
</center>


<h3>CROATIA</h3>

The <b>International Monetary Fund</b> (IMF) has approved a loan of US$103 million to Croatia. <p>

Croatia's industrial production increased by 5.1 per cent in the first three months of 1995. Production of 
raw materials increased by 6.6 per cent, equipment by 4.2 per cent and of consumer goods by 3.6 per cent 
according to the <b>State Institute for Statistics</b>.<p> 

The sale of 24.9 per cent of the equity of the <b>Pliva</b> pharmaceutical company, due to take place on 
May 8th was postponed indefinitely due to the shelling of Zagreb by Serbian forces. <p>
<hr>
<center><img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="besummy.html">Summary Menu</a></center>

