<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>MOLDOVA</h3>

Maverick 14th Army commander General Alexander Lebed threatened to resign once too often at the end 
of May over Moscow plans to downgrade his force and withdraw it from Moldova's Trans Dnestr region. 
The Russian Defence Ministry accepted the resignation and has promised Moldova that the 14th army 
troops will be withdrawn over a three-year period. 
<p>
<b>Air Moldova</b> has started a twice weekly service from Chisinau to Sofia. 
<p>
<hr>
<center><img src="images/pinred.gif" alt="*"> <a href="besummy.html">Summary Menu</a></center>

