<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#FF0000" alink="#000000" vlink="#0000ff">
<center><i><font size=+2>S</font><font size=+1>ummer 1995.</i></font></center><br>
<h3>UKRAINE</h3>

A constitutional deadlock over the division of powers between the president and parliament was ended at 
the beginning of June when the two sides signed a `constitutional treaty' under which President Kuchma's 
authority to appoint ministers and issue decrees is enhanced. The deal is for a one-year period pending the 
introduction of a new constitution. 
<p>
The <b>European Union</b> has agreed to grant the Ukraine a balance of payments loan of up to Ecu22 
million. The loan will be subject to the same conditions as the Ukraine's stand-by agreement with the 
<b>IMF</b> and to the eventual closure of the <b>Chernobyl</b> nuclear plant. The loan adds up to one 
third of Ukraine's net borrowing requirement of US$900 million in 1995. 
<p>
Deputy coal industry minister Dmitry Peresenyuk announced in May the closure of 19 unprofitable coal 
mines by 1 July. Production for 1995 is forecast at 100 million tonnes, up from the 1994 figure of 94.4 
million tonnes. 
<p>
A 17 company consortium lead by Swiss-Swedish engineering group <b>Asea Brown Boveri</b> (ABB) 
has submitted proposals costing US$3.7 billion for the closure of the <b>Chernobyl</b> nuclear plant 
reactors and their replacement with gas turbines. 
<p>
New currency legislation introduced in April states that `non-resident employers must pay their Ukrainian 
resident employees only in Ukrainian currency'. The move looks likely to fuel dissatisfaction among 
locally recruited staff hitherto paid in foreign currency. And that's not all. New tax legislation means that 
employees of non-resident companies will also cease to benefit from a 50 per cent tax concession. 
<p>
<b>Ukraine International</b> airlines is reintroducing its (summer) seasonal Manchester-Kiev service. 
<p>
Ukraine has a new telephone dialling code. The former Soviet prefix is dropped, to be replaced with 380. 
Kiev is now 44 instead of 044.
<p> 
