<P>
<a name="Topin"></a>
<h3>Top Insurance Companies</h3>
The Bulgarian insurance industry is dominated by the State Insurance 
Institute (SII) founded in 1946. It has 110 branches and covers most of 
the country. With an annual income of Lev1,600 million, SII deals with all 
types of insurance. In 1989, a new division of SII - the International 
Insurance Division - was set up to deal with foreign insurance and 
reinsurance in the areas such as cargo insurance, property, shipping, 
aviation, all risks cover, and hotel liability. Bulstrad, founded in 1961, 
deals with foreign insurance matters.
<P>
