<P>
<a name="Currency"></a>
<h3>Currency Regulations</H3>
In 1992 the lev remained as an non fully convertible currency and full 
convertibility was not expected in the short term. Banks and exchange 
bureaux are permitted to trade in convertible currency. To finance imports, 
foreign exchange can be purchased from the banks on presentation of 
certifying documents. Internal payments are made in levs although companies 
can keep hard currency accounts outside the country. 
<P>
