<P>

<P>
<h3>Roads</h3>
Bulgaria has 36,935 km roads of which 33,766 are hard surfaced. There are 
240 km of motorways. In 1992 little progress was made with the much needed 
development of the road network. However, the European Bank for 
Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) has granted a US$43 million loan for 
construction and repair on the country's roads and motorways. This is to be 
part of a US$105 million project. Monies would be directed to the completion 
of a 32 km stretch of international motorway between Plovdiv and Orizovo. 
These funds would also be used for upgrading some 800 km of primary roads 
serving regional and long distance transit traffic. The project was also 
designed to support a toll road operation on the existing motorway network. 
This was considered to be a first stage in promoting longer term private 
sector participation in the motorway construction.
<P>
Freight traffic between January and September 1992 stood at 106 million 
tonnes (down 28 per cent on the same period in the previous year) passenger 
traffic 1,336 million people (down by 2 per cent). Rail and air transport 
actually carried more people in 1992 than 1991.
</B>
<P>
