<html>
	<head>
		<title>About Worth OnLine</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/whitebarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.worth.com/forums/index.html+Worth2.gif+>
<img src="/ads/Worth2.gif" border=3 width=374 height=45 alt="Worth - Financial Intelligence"></a>

		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=6><b>About Worth OnLine</b></font><br>
		</center>
				
				
					<font size=4>
						<br><b>Welcome to Worth OnLine, the daily site from <i>Worth</i> magazine.</b><p>
If you're familiar with <i>Worth</i>, you already know that this is the place to find financial intelligence. By coming online, you get a bonus--daily market snapshots that will help you better understand what's happening in the world of money and finance
.<p>
<b>WORTH ONLINE DAILY FEATURES</b><p>
One of the first things you'll notice when you log onto our site is our new look. That's financial titan and frequent <i>Worth</i> contributor Peter Lynch gracing our opening screen. But we didn't simply slap on a new coat of paint.<p>
On the homescreen, you'll find a mix of articles from this month's <i>Worth</i> magazine and exclusive Worth OnLine columns and features. We'll post new stories every day, so you'll want to visit the site frequently to stay up-to-date:<p>
*Greg Millman, author of "The Vandals' Crown: How Rebel Currency Traders Overthrew the World's Central Banks," will kick off each Monday with "The Market Week Ahead."<p>
*Looking for a new ideas about how to search for stocks? Don't miss Tuesday's "Stock Screen of the Week."<p>
*On Thursday, top Wall Street experts will pick stocks they are eyeing or avoiding in "Pick/Pan of the Week."<p>
<b>WORTH ONLINE COLUMNS</b><p>
<i>Worth</i> staffers will be regularly contributing columns exclusively for online readers:<p>
*Tom Nawrocki, <i>Worth</i>'s "Personal Adviser" editor, writes about the business of sports in his biweekly column, "Ballpark Figures." He's covered everything from the odds of winning the NCAA office betting pool by naming all the tourney winners (nine 
point two quintillion to one) to ways to buy and buy into a major-league team (got $100 million lying around?).<p>
*Jim Melloan takes a look at trends in space, online, and everywhere in between for his monthly online-exclusive column, "Investing in the Future." <p>
*Other <i>Worth</i> editors will be popping up regularly with their two cents about investing trends, celebrities and their money, and more.<p>
<b>WORTH ONLINE RESOURCES</b><p>
Once you've caught up with today's news, head over to <a href="/departments/departments.html">DEPARTMENTS</a>, our virtual file cabinet of investor resources. It's filled with items that will help you manage and maximize your money, and get the most out o
f Worth OnLine.<p>
*Look for the complete collection of articles written for <i>Worth</i> by one of the world's foremost financial observers, <a href="/articles/PL0.html">Peter Lynch</a>.<p>
*If you're a novice investor, or a seasoned pro who wants a refresher course, Investor 101 will help you build a solid foundation of investment knowledge.<p>
*<a href="/articles/PIO.html">Investor Help Desk</a href> is the place to go if you are trying to locate unclaimed property, have a complaint against a bank, or need help starting an arbitration.<p>
*In the <a href="articles/PZO.html">Archives</a href> department, you can search our exhaustive database of articles by keyword, topic, or date. We'll recap some popular and practical features from past issues and highlight them.<p>
<b>SPECIAL EVENTS ON WORTH ONLINE</b><p>
Our live chat show, "Conference Call," feature top money managers, financial journalists, and experts from a variety of fields, including taxes, real estate, and collectibles, who answer your questions. <p>
(These events are curretly being held only on our AOL site.  Until we begin hosting them on the web, you can access transcripts of all Worth OnLine's live events in the Transcripts drawer in the Departments area of our site.)<p>
For a calendar of special events and a rundown of each week's features, sign up for our <b><i>free</i></b> weekly E-mail newsletter, <i><a href="/departments/newsletter.html">A Week's Worth</a></i>.Simply click on the "What's in Store" button in the lower
 righthand corner of the homescreen.<p>
As always, we'd like to hear from you. You can talk with <i>Worth</i> and Worth OnLine in our <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a>, or E-mail us directly at <a href="mailto:info@worth.com">info@worth.com</a>.<p>
We hope that you'll find Worth OnLine entertaining and enlightening. Come back often. It's Worth Every Day. <p>
NOTE: The photo of Peter Lynch on the opening screen was taken by Janette Beckman. Stylist, Ellen Silverstein; hair/makeup, Jim Crawford.
					</font>
					<p>
					<font size=4>
					<blockquote>
