	</td><td width=150 valign=top>
			
<center>
	<a href="index.html">
		<IMG SRC="../imgs/messagewhite.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a>
		<p>
		</center>
<b>
	 The Worth OnLine message board provides
a forum for exchanging ideas about money, finance, and Worth
magazine--"financial intelligence," if you will. 
	</b><p>
	</font>

Though we hope that all
who post messages on the board will do so responsibly, we can't guarantee
the quality of the information provided by contributors, nor the wisdom of
the opinions they express. We can't vouch for the motives of those who
post messages to the board, nor can we routinely review or investigate
their factual claims. In fact, you may well read a given posting to the
message board before anyone at Worth does. *Take what you find here with a
grain of salt.*
<p>
Messages posted are not reviewed, investigated, confirmed
or endorsed by Worth; they reflect only the views of subscribers, who are
solely responsible for their content. If you have a problem with a
posting, we suggest that you respond to it. We invite you to bring any
posting you believe to be innacurate to the attention of the Worth OnLine
staff. Please <a href="mailto:WorthOnLne@aol.com">forward</a> a copy of the posting and an explanation of your
objection to Worth OnLine.
<p>
Neither <i>Worth</i> magazine nor Worth OnLine is intended to replace the
services of professional investment advisors. Even the information
provided by representatives of Worth should not be relied on in lieu of
professional investment advice. There is no substitute for healthy
skepticism and your own good judgment. 
<p>
