<html>
	<head>
		<title>Investor 101</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/whitebarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Investor%20101>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=6><b>Investor 101</b></font><br>
		</center>
				
				
					<font size=4>
						<p>*<a href="B02.html">Due Diligence, Part 1</a> and <a href="B03.html">Part 2</a>, shows you how to make sense of a financial statement, by Jonathan Burton. <p>
 *P/E, that's  price-to-earnings ratio, not phys-ed., writes Elizabeth Macdonald in her article,<a href="B05.html">"When P/E Doesn't Mean Gym Class"</a>, about this essential analytical tool.  <p><p>
 *In <a href="B07.html">Technical Tool Chest: Part 1</a> and <a href="B08.html">Part 2</a>, Jonathan Butler covers the basic charts and formulas used by  technical investors.   <p><p>
*Ken Kurson serves up a Worth OnLine exclusive:<a href="PZOL07.html">Money Changes Everything</a>, the column that will help you build a solid foundation of investment knowledge.<p><p>
*Investor 101 also contains straightforward, sensible articles on <a href="/articles/B01.html">convertibles</a>, <a href="/articles/B04.html">the bond market</a>, <a href="/articles/B06.html">yield curves</a>, and <a href="/articles/Z9401F02.html">401(k)s</a>. <br><br>Be sure to check in regularly--we'll be adding new material all the time. <p>  <p>
					</font>
					<p>
					<font size=4>
					<blockquote>
					</blockquote>
					</font>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/investor101white.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<b>
					Whether you're learning the basics of investing, or just want a refresher course, Investor 101 is the place to be.

					</b>
	
		
