	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=6><b>Investor Help Desk</b></font><br>
		</center>
				
				
					<font size=4>
						<p>
Welcome to the Worth OnLine Investor Help Desk. In this drawer you'll find a host of resources to help you avoid or resolve problems with financial-services providers.  <p>
 *Have you ever found an unexplained service charge on your bank statement that the institution would not rescind or explain to your satisfaction? Check out the <a href="/articles/I01.html">"Banking"</a> folder for some helpful Web sites, addresses, and phone numbers.  <p>
 *If you've been victimized by an investment adviser or telemarketer, take your complaint to the North American Securities Administrators Association, Inc. Click on <a href="/articles/I02.html">"NASAA"</a> for a list of the organization's offices in all 50 states.  <p>
 *In Worth magazine's monthly <a href="/articles/PZMS25.html">"Advocate"</a> column, we assist readers in getting action on their complaints against brokers, banks, mutual funds, and the like. The Advocate archive appears here. <p>
 *In 1995, more than $2 billion in abandoned property was reported across the U.S. Only one-third of it was claimed by legal claimants. You may be owed money that you've forgotten about (like a utility deposit) or don't even know about (perhaps money in a deceased relative's safe-deposit box). Worth OnLine shows you how to retrieve it in the <a href="/articles/I03.html">"Unclaimed Property"</a> folder.  
					</font>
					<p>
					<font size=4>
					<blockquote>
					</blockquote>
					</font>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

