	<head>
		<title>Smart Consumer</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/whitebarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Smart%20Consumer>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=6><b>Smart Consumer</b></font><br>
		</center>
				
				
					<font size=4>
						 *Did you know that some auto leases could allow you to realize a profit when you return the car? Click here to find out how to get <a href="/articles/Z9702A01.html">"The Most From the Least"</a><p>
*Looking for airfare bargains? It all depends on when you buy (read <a href="/articles/Z9606A01.html">"All in the Timing"</a>) or who you buy from (check out <a href="/articles/Z9701A02.html">"Flying Under the Radar"</a>).<p>
*With tips in <a href="/articles/Z9610A05.html">"Expat, Phone Home"</a>, find out how you can avoid those extra charges that show up on your bill after you call the U.S. from a foreign country.<p>
*The rich don't get any richer by using the phones in their hotel rooms (lobby pay phones are cheaper) or renting trucks on weekends (midweek, off-season, thank you). Click here for more <a href="/articles/Z9609A04.html">"Tightwad Tips for Millionaires"</a>.<p>
*The language used in many consumer documents is cumbersome and confusing. <a href="/articles/Z9604A04.html">"Lost in the Translation"</a>tells you what you need to know.<p>
 *Another kind of card--dining--is the subject of <a href="/articles/C05.html">"The Art of the Meal."</a>  <p>
 *Buying a new home? Then don't miss our story on new-home warranties called <a href="/articles/C02.html">"Cracks in the Foundation."</a> You might be surprised to learn that you don't always get what you pay for--in fact, that warranty may be completely worthless.  <p>
 *Stay online to find the best deal on a car lease. <a href="/articles/C07.html">"Hit the Info Highway"</a> shows you where to point your mouse.  <p>
 *You wouldn't neglect your physical health. So don't be a couch potato when it comes to your finances. Take a look at <a href="/articles/C08.html">"Yearly Financial Checkup"</a> for eight tips that may save you a bundle.
					</font>
					<p>
					<font size=4>
					<blockquote>
						<a href="C09.html">Scouting the Web</a><br>
						<a href="C04.html">Dialing Deals</a><br>
						<a href="C01.html">1 Rm W/Ocean Vu to Rent Cheap</a><br>
					</blockquote>
					</font>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/smartwhite.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<b>
					Want to be a savvier shopper, smarter diner, more conscientious phone customer? We've combed the Worth archives and culled eight stories that will help make you wealthier and wiser. Wherever possible, we've updated information such as phone numbers and statistics.
					</b>
	
		
</td>
