<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 97/02/05--Taxing Tax Sites</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Daily%20Exclusives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>

				<img src="/imgs/c-WOW.gif">	
				<p>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/02/05--Taxing Tax Sites</b></font><br>
				<font size=4><br>By Ellen DePasquale</font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i>Need technical support for your tax software? Don't come calling on the Internet.</i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Tax preparation software programs are very popular, and this year's versions are better than ever. The top three tax preparation software programs include, Intuit's <a href="http://www.intuit.com/turbotax/">"TurboTax"</a>, Block Financial Corp.'s <a href="http://www.conductor.com/software/techsupp.htm>"Kiplinger TaxCut"</a>, and Parsons Technology's <a href="http://www.parsonstech.com/">"Personal Tax Edge"</a>. <p>
Each has a Web site offering product information and tax advice. But if you need technical support, don't come calling on the Internet.<p>
<p><a name="SUB1"><b><font size=+1>Intuit's site is complex, but its product search function is spotty.</font></b><p><p>
Intuit's site covers all of its products and offers seemingly good tech support search capabilities. However, since there are so many Intuit programs, simple searches become complex, and several of them did not even work. <p>
<p><hr noshade size=1>
<center><font size=+1><i><b>
Block's site, although simpler to navigate than Intuit's, does not offer much in technical support.<br>
</font></i></b></center>
<hr noshade size=1><p>
<p>
The "Top Questions" search asked me to select a product and then "Go." Nothing happened. And when I looked for another way to reach these Qs and As, I couldn't find one. The next search required me to select a product (or the "all products" option) and type in a keyword. This search worked well and found a lengthy list of forms and information about my keyword. Lastly, I tried to browse topics after selecting a product. But alas, the feature was inoperable. <p>
The tax advice on Intuit's site--including guides on "How To Survive an Audit" and "How To Avoid an Audit"--is useful. It also offers plain English descriptions of the 1996 tax changes and a calendar of important filing dates for 1997.<p>
<p><a name="SUB2"><b><font size=+1>Block provides a list of tech support phone numbers.</font></b><p><p>
Block's site is simpler to navigate than Intuit's, but it's not very deep in its technical support offerings. For instance, the "Commonly Asked Questions" link lists less than 20 questions. <p>
The site does address "Known Problems & Updates," as well as offer users the opportunity to E-mail their questions to the company. They also supply a list of tech support telephone numbers. <p>
<p><a name="SUB3"><b><font size=+1>Parson's programmers offer useful tips on using their software.</font></b><p><p>
Parsons Technology has a site full of information and heavy-duty graphics. But I had to wait forever to find anything worth reading. However, when the pages finally loaded I was pleasantly surprised by the amount of information I got. <p>
The best stuff was the <a href="http://204.42.80.117/ref/ptetips.html">program tips</a>, written by the software's programmers and developers. It is a long road to get there but the tips go on forever. These can be useful if you are confused about the field colors, certain keystrokes, and other software features.<p>
The tax advice includes 1996 tax legislation and links to separate pages for information on topics such as car expense, home used as business, and IRS audit selection criteria. Again, be prepared to wait a while before you arrive at the final page of information. <p>
[Post your questions and comments on the <a href="/forums/findit/site/worthboard.html">"Web Site of the Week"</a> message board.]<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
