<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - MESSAGE BOARD GUIDELINES</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.worth.com/forums/index.html+Worth2.gif+>
<img src="/ads/Worth2.gif" border=3 width=374 height=45 alt="Worth - Financial Intelligence"></a>

		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>MESSAGE BOARD GUIDELINES</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						PURPOSE OF THE MESSAGE BOARD: Worth OnLine's message board is an open forum to talk about matters of money and finance. It's also a place to discuss Worth stories, or post questions or comments to other Worth OnLine users. If you're looking for info
rmation on something, post a message; chances are someone at Worth or another user may have some helpful thoughts.<p>
THE RIGHT WAY TO POST A MESSAGE: Before you post a message, please look over all the forums and choose the most appropriate one. This helps keep ongoing discussions on track, and it usually brings the speediest response to your message. (If we happen upon
 a posting that's off a folder's topic, we may move or delete it to keep things organized.) Also, please keep in mind that the message board is intended to serve as an open forum, not just another way of E-mailing someone at Worth. Other users will be rea
ding your posting, so whenever you refer to a specific company, stock, or even a story from Worth, please provide enough information in your posting so that other users reading it will understand what you're talking about.<p>
PROBLEMATIC POSTINGS: Messages posted by subscribers are not reviewed, investigated, confirmed or endorsed by Worth; they reflect only the views of subscribers, who are solely responsible for their content. If you have a problem with a posting, we suggest
 that you respond to it. We invite you to bring any posting you believe to be inaccurate to the attention of the Worth OnLine staff. Please forward a copy of the posting and an explanation of your objection to <a href="mailto:WorthOnLne@aol.com">WorthOnLn
e</a>.<p>
THE ROLE OF <a href="/articles/H03.html">WORTH ONLINE EDITORS</a>: The message board also offers a way to tap the expertise of Worth's staff. Worth editors can help you track down additional details related to stories published in the magazine. And if we 
don't have the information you're looking for, we can also tell you about resources that can help you find your own answers. Keep in mind, though, that the primary role of Worth's staff is to serve as moderators for the public discussion online. While we'
re happy to chat about the market or the financial world in general, we're not going to advise you to choose a particular course of action regarding your finances. Neither will we recommend a specific security.<p>
Neither Worth magazine nor Worth OnLine is intended to replace the services of professional investment advisors. Even the information provided by representatives of Worth should not be relied on in lieu of professional investment advice. There is no subst
itute for healthy skepticism and your own good judgment. <p>
If you're having a problem with a financial-service provider, consider taking it to the Worth Advocate for help. To contact the Advocate, send E-mail to <a href="mailto:WAdvocate@aol.com">WAdvocate@aol.com</a>.<p>
ADVERTISING: The message board is intended for people to share ideas freely. It is not a place for advertisements or purely promotional postings. Messages including solicitations that are brought to our attention will be deleted.<p>
AND ANOTHER THING: A final note, please be respectful of other users. Though we hope that all who post messages to the board will do so responsibly, we can't guarantee the quality of the information provided by contributors, nor the wisdom of the opinions
 they express. We can't vouch for the motives of those who post messages to the board, nor can we routinely review or investigate their factual claims. In fact, you may well read a given posting to the message board before anyone at Worth does. *Take what
 you find here with a grain of salt.*<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

