<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - About Worth Magazine</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.worth.com/+Worth1.gif+>
<img src="/ads/Worth1.gif" border=3 width=374 height=45 alt="Worth - Financial Intelligence"></a>

		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>About Worth Magazine</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Worth is a different kind of personal finance magazine. We believe that intelligent investors need more than just a series of commands to buy this or that financial product. We think it's important to understand the trends, the institutions, the mar

keting ploys, and the inside economics of individual companies so that you'll know why a course of action makes sense.<p>
Times have changed. Twenty years ago, investors had to struggle to find any financial information beyond the stock tables. Today most investors are faced with too much information. Our task at Worth is to help you sort through it all. <p>
We also believe that it's important to take a wider view of personal finance than do most of the other magazines covering this field. Too often, financial advisors speak to us as if we were just cold-bloodedly rational financial machines. It's easy to sug

gest a portfolio full of risk to a 45-year-old, but another thing to execute that plan.<p>
As much as Worth readers are concerned with making and keeping and investing money, they are concerned with their families, their jobs, their relationships, and their communities. In other words, at Worth we believe that personal finance must include the 

personal as well as the financial.
<p>
If you want to reach us via the U.S. Postal system, write to:
<p>
Worth Magazine<br>
575 Lexington Avenue<br>
35th Floor<br>
New York, NY 10022<br>
<p>
Or, call us at (212) 751-4550.
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

